      Oh Elon
   =20
 =20
On Monday morning Elon Musk filed a Schedule 13G disclosing that he owned 9=
.2% of=C2=A0Twitter Inc., which was  a fun surprise. Part of the fun was th=
at a 13G is a form that is used by=C2=A0passive=C2=A0investors who do not p=
lan to meddle with the company=E2=80=99s management, and that doesn=E2=80=
=99t sound like Elon Musk. Activist investors are supposed to use the more =
detailed Schedule 13D. But Musk=C2=A0checked the passive investor box. Fun =
choice.Part of the fun was that Musk=E2=80=99s 13G seemed to be late? It se=
emed to say that Musk acquired 5% of Twitter=E2=80=99s stock on March 14, a=
nd under the rules he would have 10 calendar days =E2=80=94=C2=A0until Marc=
h 24 =E2=80=94=C2=A0to file the 13G (or 13D). But he filed it on April 4, 1=
1 days late.On Tuesday afternoon Elon Musk filed a Schedule 13D disclosing =
that he owns 9.1% of Twitter. So! This does not=C2=A0necessarily=C2=A0prove=
 that he should have filed a 13D in the first place, or that=C2=A0his inten=
tions were activist-y all along. Between Monday morning and Tuesday afterno=
on, various things changed. Musk tweeted a poll about adding an edit button=
 to Twitter? Also Twitter announced that he was  joining its board of direc=
tors? He was just buying stock as a passive investment, he disclosed his st=
ake, Twitter called him up and said =E2=80=9Chey I see you bought our stock=
, would you like to join the board,=E2=80=9D he was like =E2=80=9CI had nev=
er thought of it but sure,=E2=80=9D they wrote up a brief agreement, he got=
 to work polling his followers about what he should do as a director, but t=
hen he said =E2=80=9Chang on though I=E2=80=99d better file a 13D, you know=
 what a stickler I am for securities regulation=E2=80=9D? I guess that is p=
ossible. He was tweeting polls about changing Twitter=E2=80=99s policies in=
 March?=C2=A0He=E2=80=99s been talking to Twitter about joining its board f=
or weeks? It all feels like a stretch. If he needed a 13D yesterday he prob=
ably needed one earlier.[1]But his 13D=C2=A0does=C2=A0prove that he should =
have filed whatever he filed=C2=A0earlier. The trading exhibit in the 13D s=
hows how many shares he bought each day: He started buying at the end of Ja=
nuary, crossed 5% on March 14, and should in fact have filed a 13G or=C2=A0=
13D on March 24. He acquired about 13.1 million shares=C2=A0after March 24,=
 at an average price of $39.06; the stock closed at $49.97 the day he annou=
nced his stake. In rough terms, he saved $143 million on those purchases by=
 filing his form late: People would have sold the stock at $50 if they=E2=
=80=99d known Musk was a big holder, and he was legally obligated to tell t=
hem, but he didn=E2=80=99t and bought at $39 instead. If I were the directo=
r of the Elon Musk Division at the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission =
I would absolutely go after him for that money![2]=C2=A0I don=E2=80=99t kno=
w why he missed the deadline? One possibility is that he just=C2=A0likes=C2=
=A0having drama with the SEC. Another=C2=A0possibility is that he was casua=
lly buying stock=C2=A0and at some point he mentioned to his lawyers =E2=80=
=9Chey FYI I own 9% of Twitter=E2=80=9D and they turned green. I do not kno=
w why his=C2=A0broker=C2=A0didn=E2=80=99t stop him? Like if you are a broke=
r and you buy 9% of a company for a guy,=C2=A0you really ought to send him =
a link to the SEC website?=C2=A0There=E2=80=99s no reason to expect Elon Mu=
sk to be conversant with beneficial-ownership filing rules (except that he=
=E2=80=99s a public-company CEO?), or to talk to lawyers voluntarily, but t=
hat is part of the broker=E2=80=99s job.Do you think he bothered to file an=
 HSR notification before buying the stock?I just feel like in much of my li=
fe around here I find out=C2=A0about stuff and think =E2=80=9Cwell what is =
the logical explanation for this=E2=80=9D and try to write it down. A deep =
thesis of this column is that, more often than many people think, it is pos=
sible to explain events in the financial world in logical and intuitive way=
s. That seems like a dangerous bias to have with Elon Musk.Oh by the way hi=
s 13G on Monday said he owned 9.2% of Twitter (73,486,938 shares), and his =
13D on Tuesday said=C2=A09.1% (73,115,038)? This discrepancy cannot really =
be explained by =E2=80=9Che sold 371,900 shares on Monday and Tuesday,=E2=
=80=9D since the 13D has to report all of his Twitter stock=C2=A0transactio=
ns in the last 60 days, and that report lists purchases of 73,115,038 share=
s and no sales.[3]=C2=A0Could the discrepancy be explained by =E2=80=9Che f=
orgot how many shares he owned=E2=80=9D?=C2=A0
