ggest a cash transaction at $60 per share=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D and providing a=
dorably (allegedly) fake financial statements:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"m=
argin: 16px 0;">Ten Cate provided Textron with Xcalibur=E2=80=99s purported=
 2019 financial statements, which claimed that its revenue more than double=
d to approximately =C2=A3360 million and its assets increased to approximat=
ely =C2=A310.3 billion, including approximately =C2=A39.8 billion in cash a=
nd cash equivalents. These 2019 financial statements were internally incons=
istent. Among other things, although Xcalibur claimed to grow from 238 empl=
oyees at year-end 2018 to 414 employees at year-end 2019, its wage and sala=
ry expenses remained =C2=A36 million and its operating costs were exactly =
=C2=A362,094,786 both years. Textron did not respond to the offer.</p></blo=
ckquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Apparently frustrated by Textron=E2=80=
